&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Mallory Alexander International Logistics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, a global third-party logistics (3PL) provider, is seeking a Logistics Professional to join our growing team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring the accurate and timely processing of customer and vendor invoices while supporting day-to-day billing and financial operations. You will work closely with internal departments and clients to resolve billing discrepancies, maintain accurate financial records, and ensure compliance with company policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate accurate and timely invoices using Excel and/or billing software, including auditing and processing customer-required coding before submission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, classify, and code vendor and utility invoices prior to payment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and resolve billing issues or discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with clients regarding invoice status, corrections, or required documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update invoicing databases to ensure data accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze financial data to identify variances and correct errors promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal departments to verify and align financial information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and enhance financial spreadsheets and reporting tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide data-driven insights to improve billing accuracy and workflow efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with company policies and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run daily reports and update dashboards as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support general financial analysis and reporting tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with light administrative duties, including travel arrangements and expense report handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in business administration, accounting or related field preferred.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a Data Analyst, Billing Analyst, or similar role in finance or accounting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Microsoft Excel skills (PivotTables, VLOOKUP, IF statements, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical mindset with high attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work efficiently under deadlines and handle multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time-management abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, written and verbal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and collaboratively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift: &lt;/strong&gt;First Shift, Monday Through Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Environment: &lt;/strong&gt;Duties regularly require employee to stand, walk, and reach with hands, talk and hear. The employee is occasionally required to stoop, kneel, crouch, or lift and/or move up to 25 pounds. Duties will require proficient use of computer, software, phone systems and other similar technology. The noise level in the work environment is usually moderate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Mallory Alexander?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
