&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Mallory Alexander International Logistics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, a global third-party logistics (3PL) provider, is seeking a Logistics Professional to join our growing team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced&lt;strong&gt; iSeries Software Developer&lt;/strong&gt; to support, enhance, and maintain warehouse management system (WMS) applications running on the IBM i (AS/400) platform. This role will work closely with operations, IT infrastructure, and business teams to develop and support warehouse, distribution, and inventory management solutions that improve efficiency and reliability across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and support IBM i / AS400 warehouse management applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and modify RPG, RPGLE, CL, SQL, and DB2 programs related to warehouse operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support WMS integrations with ERP systems, handheld RF devices, barcode scanners, shipping systems, and third-party logistics providers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot production issues and provide timely resolution for warehouse and distribution operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in system upgrades, testing, deployments, and change management processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain technical documentation for applications, interfaces, and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with warehouse operations teams to identify process improvements and automation opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor system performance and ensure application stability and data integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with after-hours support as needed for critical warehouse operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of IBM i (AS400/iSeries) development experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or related field preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with RPG IV / RPGLE, CL, SQL, and DB2 for i.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting or developing Warehouse Management Systems (WMS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of inventory control, shipping, receiving, picking, packing, and distribution processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with EDI, APIs, or system integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong troubleshooting and analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and teamwork abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in-office Monday through Friday in Memphis, TN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. Occasional after-hours or weekend support may be required during implementations or critical outages.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Mallory Alexander?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mallory Alexander International Logistics is a leading full-service logistics provider established in 1925. With more than 10 facilities in the U.S. and 3 in Asia, Mallory Alexander supports manufacturers, retailers and other suppliers in the storage and shipment of their valuable cargo, and we do it with confidence–on time, with care, everywhere. We proudly offer competitive compensation, robust benefits and a family environment, an environment where our dedicated employees are able make an impact on our customers&#39; experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you are based in California, we encourage you to read this important information for California residents linked &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mallorygroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/CCP

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Mallory Alexander International Logistics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, a global third-party logistics (3PL) provider, is seeking a Logistics Professional to join our growing team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will serve as the primary point of contact for customers, overseas agents, and business partners, helping ensure ocean import shipments move smoothly from start to finish. You will play a key role in providing excellent customer service, coordinating shipment details, and maintaining accurate, up-to-date shipment information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Duties and Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and manage ocean import shipments from booking through final delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor shipment status and proactively track cargo movement from origin to destination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and trace shipments to ensure departure and ensuring all U.S. customs manifest formalities have been fulfilled by internal departments managing filings (e.g. AMS or ISF filings).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with overseas agents, steamship lines, customs brokers, trucking companies, warehouses, and customers to ensure smooth shipment execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare, verify, and transmit arrival notices and delivery instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all destination handling fees are paid so shipments can be picked up within free time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve shipment delays, holds, demurrage, detention, and other operational issues promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report delays or any disruptions to our customers, including the appropriate customer service account manager and supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with customs brokerage department to provide documentation for entry preparation and transmission upon receipt of clearance documents from overseas agent and/or importer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate shipment files and documentation in accordance with company and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update operating system with associated milestones and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with accounting regarding billing discrepancies, credit holds, and customer invoicing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned by Ocean Import Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in ocean import freight forwarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of sea carrier practices, Incoterms, import documentation, and international trade regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational, communication, and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with freight forwarding systems (CargoWise experience preferred) and Microsoft Office applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and deadlines in a fast-paced environment, both on a team and independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;PDq2pG_selectionAnchorContainer&quot; data-start=&quot;587&quot; data-end=&quot;846&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;587&quot; data-end=&quot;605&quot;&gt;Pay &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br data-start=&quot;605&quot; data-end=&quot;608&quot;&gt;We offer a competitive hourly rate of $28.00–$31.00, depending on your experience. You&#39;ll also receive a comprehensive benefits package that includes medical, dental, and vision insurance, a 401(k) plan, and paid time off (PTO).&lt;/p&gt;
